This is short installation instructions for Picket
(http://sourceforge.net/projects/picket).

1. Install Python (http://python.org/).

2. Install Django (http://www.djangoproject.com/).

3. Checkout latest revision of Picket from Subversion repository from here:
http://sourceforge.net/svn/?group_id=210642

4. Change working directory to the root directory of your local Picket copy.

5. Copy file "settings_sample.py" to "settings.py" and edit it if you need.

6. Run in terminal for making default database file:
$ ./manage.py syncdb

7. Run in terminal for start picket:
$ ./manage.py runserver

8. Point your browser at:
http://localhost:8000/

You are done!

Please report any bugs here:
http://sourceforge.net/tracker/?group_id=210642&atid=1014558
